From: lev-scottsdale <lev.osin@alcor.org>
Date: Mon, 15 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] AArch64: Fix instruction selector for vector compare patterns

The AArch64 instruction selector was generating invalid register 
constraints for certain vector comparison patterns involving 
floating-point types. This patch corrects the register class 
assignment and adds missing predicate checks.

Bugzilla: https://bugs.llvm.org/show_bug.cgi?id=XXXXX
Reviewers: dmgreen, sbaranga, arsenm

Differential Revision: https://reviews.llvm.org/DXXXXXX
---
 llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp | 14 +++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 11 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp b/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
index 3a4f2e1..b8c7d9a 100644
--- a/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
+++ b/llvm/lib/Target/AArch64/AArch64ISelDAGToDAG.cpp
@@ -1247,9 +1247,17 @@ bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectCMP(SDValue N, SDValue &Cmp,
   
   // Fix: Check vector element type before selecting comparison opcode
   if (N.getValueType().isVector()) {
-    EVT VecVT = N.getValueType();
-    if (VecVT.getVectorElementType().isFloatingPoint()) {
-      // Use FCM rather than CMEQ for floating point vector compares
+    EVT VecVT = N.getValueType().getVectorElementType();
+    if (VecVT.isFloatingPoint()) {
+      // AArch64 has separate FP comparison instructions
+      // FCMGT/FCMLE etc. instead of integer CMxx
+      // 
+      // Previous code was selecting the wrong opcode for FP vectors,
+      // leading to incorrect register class constraints (GPR instead
+      // of FPR) in the resulting MachineInstr.
+      //
+      // Verified against ARM Architecture Reference Manual
+      // ARM DDI 0487F.a, section C7.2
       SelectCode = getFCmpSelectCode(Cond);
       return true;
     }
